  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Solstice FilterMate, what fails, how, and what to do about it</h2>
      <p>
        FilterMate is Pitco's integrated auto-filtration system on the Solstice Supreme flagship, and it's the
        single biggest differentiator between Pitco Solstice and the SG/SE base configurations. FilterMate works
        by running a pump to drive used fryer oil through a filter paper and O-ring-sealed manifold, then returning
        clean oil back to the fryer tank. The pump and paper handle the filtration; the O-ring manifold seals the
        flow path; the manifold valves control filter-cycle timing. When operating properly, FilterMate runs
        multiple filtration cycles per service day without operator intervention and significantly extends oil
        life.
      </p>
      <p>
        The failure cascade we see most often in LA service calls, roughly in order of frequency:
      </p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li><b>Filter paper misfeeding or tearing</b>, wrong paper spec, paper loaded backwards, paper degraded
          from extended storage. Symptom: auto-filter cycle runs but oil returns contaminated, or pump motor
          over-runs trying to push oil through a blocked paper. Service: paper replacement with correct Pitco spec,
          pump manifold cleaning. 30–45 minutes.</li>
        <li><b>O-ring seal degradation</b>, the manifold O-rings age, harden, and lose seal over time. Symptom:
          oil bypass (clean oil mixed with used oil), external oil leakage around the manifold, or pump
          over-pressure indicators. Service: O-ring kit replacement, manifold seal verification. 45–90 minutes.</li>
        <li><b>Filter pump motor wear or failure</b>, the pump motor bearings wear from continuous operation, or
          the motor winding fails from over-load conditions. Symptom: pump stall, intermittent pump operation, or
          complete pump failure. Service: motor replacement, pump assembly inspection. 60–90 minutes.</li>
        <li><b>Pump manifold clogging from carbonized oil</b>, when Pitco's weekly FilterMate cleaning protocol
          is skipped, carbonized oil buildup accumulates in the manifold pathways. Symptom: slow filtration cycles,
          reduced oil return volume, eventual pump stall. Service: deep manifold cleaning, possibly manifold
          replacement on severely neglected units. 90–180 minutes depending on buildup severity.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Most FilterMate service calls trace back to skipped weekly cleaning, the mechanism works reliably when
        maintained on Pitco's recommended schedule, and it starts degrading quickly when operators push maintenance
        to monthly or quarterly cadence. We coach operators on the proper protocol during service calls and set
        PM schedules on accounts that want proactive maintenance to avoid the cascade failures.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

