      <h2>LA gas regulator calibration, CARB + LADBS compliance</h2>
      <p>
        Pitco gas fryers (Solstice Supreme, SG, SSH, SFSG, Compa gas, Multi-Battery gas) all require proper gas
        regulator calibration. The regulator, the pressure-reducing device between your building gas supply and
        the fryer, has to be matched to the specific appliance spec accounting for natural-gas or propane service,
        building supply pressure, and appliance modulation range. In California, this work falls under the CSLB
        BHGS license, CARB emissions compliance, and LADBS permitting in most commercial
        contexts.
      </p>
      <p>
        For Pitco Solstice Supreme specifically, regulator calibration matters more than on simpler fryer designs
        because the FilterMate system's oil-temperature stability depends on consistent burner performance across
        the fryer's modulation range. Regulator drift shows up as oil temperature instability, fryer oil running
        hotter or colder than the set point, which trickles directly into food quality, cook-time consistency,
        and in worst-case, unsafe food temperatures. Our techs verify regulator calibration on every Pitco gas
        service call and document the verified values in the work order. CARB Title 20 rebate programs through
        SoCal Gas and LA utilities occasionally make regulator-plus-appliance retrofits financially attractive for
        older kitchens; we can advise during service.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

